<div class="idea-header">
<p style="color: var(--primary-accent);font-weight:600;text-transform:uppercase;">Neuroscience</p>
<h1 class="idea-title">Neuroplasticity</h1>
<p style="font-size:1.05rem;color:var(--gray-text);line-height:1.8;">The brain's remarkable ability to adapt, reorganize, and grow throughout life.</p>
</div>
<div class="media-placeholder">
<iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/OHK8SB9elOw?si=feE46Ponpe9A41WV" title="YouTube video player" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
</div>
<div class="content-section"><h3>Key Concepts</h3><ul class="key-concepts">
<li>Synaptic Plasticity: The ability of connections between neurons to become stronger or weaker through experience and learning.</li>
<li>Neural Pathways: Networks of neurons that transmit information and are continuously reshaped by practice and repetition.</li>
<li>Long-Term Potentiation: A lasting increase in communication between neurons that supports learning and memory.</li>
<li>Neurogenesis: The formation of new neurons in specific brain regions throughout life.</li>
</ul></div>
<div class="content-section"><h3>Vocabulary</h3><div class="vocabulary">
<div class="vocab-item"><strong>Adapt (C1)</strong><span>To change in order to become more suitable for a new situation.</span></div>
<div class="vocab-item"><strong>Reinforce (C1)</strong><span>To make something stronger.</span></div>
<div class="vocab-item"><strong>Resilient (C2)</strong><span>Able to recover quickly from difficulties.</span></div>
<div class="vocab-item"><strong>Stimulus (C1)</strong><span>Something that causes activity or a response.</span></div>
<div class="vocab-item"><strong>Acquire (C1)</strong><span>To gain knowledge or a skill.</span></div>
</div></div>
<div class="content-section"><h3>Big Question</h3><div class="big-question">"If the brain is constantly rewiring itself, how much of who we are is truly fixed?"</div></div>
<div class="content-section"><h3>Questions to Explore</h3><ul class="key-concepts">
<li>How does learning a new skill physically change the brain?</li>
<li>Can neuroplasticity help people recover after brain injuries?</li>
<li>Why does repetition strengthen neural connections?</li>
</ul></div>
